record_data.record_title: Reactive Supply and Voltage Control from Generation Sources
record_data.record_plain_text:
ONEENERGY BAKER POINT SOLAR, LLC RATE SCHEDULE FERC NO. 1
Reactive Supply and Voltage Control from Generation Sources Service
OneEnergy Baker Point Solar, LLC ("BPS") provides Reactive Supply and Voltage Control from Generation Sources Service ("Reactive Supply Service") from a solar-powered generating facility located in Frederick County, Maryland within the Potomac Edison Company ("PEC") zone of the control area administered by PJM Interconnection, L.L.C. ("PJM") in order to assist in maintaining transmission voltages within acceptable limits on the PJM transmission system. This Rate Schedule sets forth BPS's revenue requirements for the provision of Reactive Supply Service, as contemplated by Schedule 2 of the PJM Open Access Transmission Tariff, which provides that PJM will pay generation owners their monthly revenue requirement for Reactive Supply Service. This Rate Schedule shall be effective upon the date authorized by the Federal Energy Regulatory Commission.
FIXED CAPABILITY REVENUE REQUIREMENT: BPS's Fixed Capability Component revenue requirement shall be calculated as follows: Fixed Annual Revenue Requirement is: $113,000.12 Monthly Revenue Requirement is: $ 9,416.67
